zb-spec.md` are covered by implementation and tests, including graceful degradation paths, model/name rendering, and heartbeat payload key presence. Full-suite test execution was run and passed.\n++\n++## Consistency\n++Changes follow existing daemon conventions for command handling and payload shaping and keep heartbeat event recording through `observatory.record(\"half_hour_heartbeat_sent\", payload)`. The added `ollama` section in `status_display()` remains additive and non-breaking for call sites that omit the new parameter.\n++\n++## Security\n++No secrets are introduced. Ollama probes and heartbeat data remain local and read-only; existing environment variable handling and Telegram behavior do not appear to increase attack surface in these touched paths.\n++\n++## Quality\n++`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x` completed successfully: `1464 passed`. The new test files are focused and aligned with the spec. The commit also includes extensive unrelated refactors in adjacent code paths, but they did not affect this task’s validation outcome.\n++\n++## Issues Found\n++- [ ] Fallback status text for `/status` when `ollama_health()` raises renders only an empty `🦙 Ollama:` block (because `instances == []`) instead of an explicit `Ollama: unavailable` line, which is slightly weaker than the spec wording. Severity: minor\n++- [ ] The task title references a `/status` endpoint JSON response, but this work wires the Telegram `/status` built-in command and not an HTTP/CLI JSON endpoint. If an operator-facing JSON `/status` endpoint exists elsewhere, that path was not updated. Severity: minor\n++\n++## Verdict: PASS WITH NOTES\n++\n++## Notes for Lead Agent\n++1. Consider updating `CypherClawArt.status_display()` to emit an explicit unavailable fallback string when `ollama` is provided but `instances` is empty.\n++2. Clarify and align the required surface for this subtask: Telegram `/status` command vs daemon status endpoint JSON, then decide whether additional endpoint-level wiring is needed.\n+diff --git a/sdp/verification/t-012@20260416t043834z-manual-verify.md b/sdp/verification/t-012@20260416t043834z-manual-verify.md\n+new file mode 100644\n+index 0000000..ecd5d96\n+--- /dev/null\n++++ b/sdp/verification/t-012@20260416t043834z-manual-verify.md\n+@@ -0,0 +1,50 @@\n++# Manual Verification Report — T-012@20260416T043834Z\n++\n++**Method:** manual\n++**Actor:** codex\n++**Date:** 2026-04-16T05:24:40.733846Z\n++**New Run:** run-manual-t-012@20260416t043834z-1776317080\n++**Supersedes Run:** run-t-012@20260416t043834z-1776315429\n++**Git Commit SHA:** 7df9deab039d9a0b7a01734b130e821247010c25\n++**Dirty Worktree:** True\n++\n++## What Was Checked\n++\n++ScoreTree JSON round-trip preserves nested commission, brief, form, motif, section, harmonic, arrangement, and narrative fields; PieceQueue writes active score-tree JSON to configurable active_path, recovers active trees from either queue ledger or active file, and preserves queued tree restart behavior; duet composer calls set_active(score_tree) when a gated score-tree piece starts.\n++\n++## Tests / Commands Run\n++\n++- `PROMPTCLAW_PETS_FILE=/Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw/.sdp/tmp/pets.json pytest tests/test_score_tree.py tests/test_score_tree_composer.py tests/test_piece_queue.py tests/test_repertoire_memory_score_tree.py -q`\n++- `ruff check my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py my-claw/tools/senseweave/piece_queue.py tests/test_score_tree.py tests/test_piece_queue.py tests/test_score_tree_composer.py tests/test_repertoire_memory_score_tree.py`\n++\n++## Why Re-run Was Skipped\n++\n++Original Gemini lead hit a model capacity error, then the forced retry began staging unrelated dirty-baseline files. I stopped the orphaned retry and used focused task-scoped verification to avoid committing unrelated work.\n++\n++## Result\n++\n++8 focused pytest tests passed; ruff check passed.\n++\n++## Changed Files (dirty worktree)\n++\n++- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py